Hi there, 


All Honors Students received an email from me asking if they would like to change Advisers on September 30th.

Please arrange a time to meet with Professor Franklin separately, or any other faculty member. Once they've signed your telebears form, I will release your Adviser Code in 205 Cory. 

Nicole

I'm in the EECS honors program, so I was automatically assigned to Professor Franklin's faculty advising session. However, this session overlaps with my class time, and I was wondering if it would be possible to switch to a different session. I tried to do this through the online system, but I couldn't figure out how to - am I missing something, or is this not possible?
history.subject: Sign up for different advising session?
